  m_Name: MiscPapers
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Papers
  spreads:
  - layout: {fileID: 6211519498159910813, guid: 274d6efd15c355843aab952415fd5afe, type: 3}
    textA: 'Anything I can''t describe in the other books will go in this one. I
      think I have seen one of them, but I could only sketch from memory.


      A
      lot of this info is from older local texts and I have no visual description
      of what they are, just what they can do.'
    textB: Perhaps they are the cause of the other creatures in the area? There's
      a lot of weird symbols in the area, perhaps worshippers?
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 4270343692058737628, guid: bf2b8e7b4bd89f043870362675472ec1, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 47b82e718860d8b4980dae3a14c78206, type: 3}
    textA: I don't know who or what this being is, I dont even know if it is from
      this realm.
    textB: 'I witnessed this one myself in deeper parts of the forest near the old
      cabins. At first I thought I was seeing things, but from what I could see he
      was altering space, and travelling through portals.


      It saw me and looked
      right at me, which is what I based my sketch from. When it looked at me (Or
      so I thought) I realised it was looking right through me, almost as if me,
      a human was so insignificant, it was looking at something else. The same way
      we walk through a forest and pay no mind to all the small bugs we walk on....'
    textC: ???
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 36e7fdfff542a154eace6a4cc52106b6, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 4469434606004700145, guid: 7c005b3cb2c21dc49bbad0344b8fd157, type: 3}
    textA: 'If you seen him don''t run!

'
    textB: 'Just hide or stay still!

'
    textC: He seems to be able to freeze time!!
    textD: I need to find more information on this being, for now all I can say is
      there's no point running, as he will catch you if he so chooses.
    imageA: {fileID: 0}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 382324df8ff70ba43858894e7d1ba04a, type: 3}
    textA: I have spent years translating this text, they speak of some sort of ancient
      being. Who knows when this was written....My translation is to the right.
    textB: "Solaris is not a creature of flesh, but of motion.\nIt does not chase.
      It does not hide.\nIt waits\u2026 and in waiting, it devours.\n\nWhere it lingers,
      time loosens its shape.\nMoments stretch. Minutes slip.\nThe world begins to
      move\u2026 faster than it should.\n\nIf you feel the hours tightening around
      you,\nit has already seen you."
    textC: Solaris
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 2916194396839415076, guid: 99fccc0fabdd3264faff0d66bfa45356, type: 3}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
  - layout: {fileID: 470820575514630869, guid: 27b86f1d9cbaee04db5d2bb6679e69ca, type: 3}
    textA: "From that translation I gather they worshipped someone, or something...called
      Solaris.\n\nAt first I thought it was something about the sun and time, but
      upon further reading it seems this being was feared and worshiped long ago...\n\nI
      havnt't seen anything on it's weaknesses. \n\nLight does nothing.\nSound does
      nothing.\nEven stillness offers no protection.\n\n"
    textB: 'I saw this passage of text:

      When time breaks,

      you must
      restore what is true.


      From what I could gather, it seems to alter our
      perception of time, and feed off that somehow.


      I recall hearing something
      about a local hiker claiming to see time alter in front of him, he looked at
      his watch and it was moving faster!


      He said as soon as he fixed his
      watch and reset it, it all stopped.

      Could the same be said for electronic
      devices?

'
    textC: 
    textD: 
    imageA: {fileID: 0}
    imageB: {fileID: 0}
    imageC: {fileID: 0}
    imageD: {fileID: 0}
